Preconditions:
The input array `tickets` must not be null.
The input array `tickets` must have at least one element.
The input array `tickets` must contain only non-negative integers.
The input integer `k` must be a valid index within the range of the input array `tickets`.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the time taken to finish buying tickets.
The returned time value is non-negative.
The returned time value is the time taken by the person at position `k` to finish buying tickets.